The ECM in Section 2.1 can be expanded to incorporate any number of cells in parallel. For this derivation, four cells with one RC pair each is used, but the methodology is generic and can be extended to any number of cells or RC pairs. Fig. 1b presents a schematic of four cells in parallel with an interconnection resistance (R

                           c
                        ) between each terminal. Each cell is represented by its own ECM as in Fig. 1a.
